 although rare for your garage door to open by itself.";i:10;s:72:"There are a few unusual factors that can cause your door open by itself.";i:11;s:42:"Here are a few scenarios weve come across.";i:12;s:144:"Residential electric garage door openers manufactured after 1993 are equipped with two safety mechanisms that operate while the door is closing.";i:13;s:56:"The first is photoelectric and the second is mechanical.";i:14;s:96:"If your garage door keeps going back up after youve closed it the most common reason is because.";i:15;s:31:"The safety sensors are blocked.";i:16;s:59:"There are safety sensors at the bottom of your garage door.";i:17;s:67:"This infrared sensor passes a beam horizontally across the opening.";i:18;s:81:"The folks who leave their garage door open 24 hours a day live across the street.";i:19;s:35:"We have an HOA in our neighborhood.";i:20;s:198:"One of the rules says that you must keep your garage door closed unless you are working in there or there are service persons doing work in there or of course if you are moving your cars in and out.";i:21;s:87:"The number three reason your Garage Door is opening randomly is your Garage Door Motor.";i:22;s:105:"Unfortunately this also happens to be the most expensive technical problem requiring an expert to fix it.";i:23;s:200:"A Electrical surges stormy weather can disrupt and damage the circuitlogic board or short circuit wiring in your Garage Door Motor effectively causing it to send the wrong signals to your Garage Door.";i:24;s:157:"It can be unnerving to hear your garage door opener run when no ones coming home or to find the garage door unexpectedly open in the morning or after a trip.";i:25;s:166:"When an automatic garage door opener opens and closes the door on its own its called phantom operation Fortunately the causes and solutions are usually fairly simple.";i:26;s:70:"In short thieves can use a device that can remotely open garage doors.";i:27;s:61:"This ABC news report from a few years ago covered this topic.";i:28;s:88:"Using rolling code technology in your garage system can help prevent this type of crime.";i:29;s:86:"Check to make sure your garage door is closed when you lock your entry doors at night.";i:30;s:168:"The remedy is as KennethR did clear all devices from your garage door by holding the learn button for 30 seconds -and reprogram all of your openers to your garage door.";i:31;s:86:"And check that no neighbors are opening their doors when your programming you openers.";i:32;s:84:"When any part of the device fails no matter how small it can affect the entire door.";i:33;s:90:"A ghost opening garage door is one problem that may indicate a problem with the mechanism.";i:34;s:95:"Below are three reasons why your garage door opens on its own and some quick fixes you can try.";i:35;s:53:"Garage doors use radio frequencies to open and close.";i:36;s:141:"The symptom of this is a garage door that is in constant motion opening fully then immediately descending only to start the same cycle again.";i:37;s:74:"There may also be loose wire connections inside the button housing itself.";i:38;s:99:"If your garage door has been opening randomly all on its own it can be frustrating and bewildering.";i:39;s:42:"Heres some fixes for this strange problem.";i:40;s:55:"Were open with new additional COVID-19 safety measures.";i:41;s:40:"Call us today toll free at 360 216-0106.";i:42;s:55:"What To Do If Your Garage Door Keeps Closing Reopening.";i:43;s:177:"The garage door is likely the most used entryway to your home and its essential to keep this fixture regularly maintained to ensure lasting safety convenience and peace of mind.";i:44;s:161:"One regular garage door issue many homeowners face is clicking the control panel to close your door only to have it immediately reopen once it reaches the floor.";i:45;s:19:"Garage Door Opener.";i:46;s:27:"Opens and closes by itself.";i:47;s:162:"When your garage door opens or closes when you havent triggered the remote